2 HOUSE BILL 237
1 (B) (1) THE APPLICATION PERIOD TO APPLY TO A CENTRAL COMMITTEE
2 TO FILL A VACANCY SHALL BE:
3 (I) OPEN FOR AT LEAST 7 DAYS; AND
4 (II) ADVERTISED IN A CONSPICUOUS MANNER BY THE CENTRAL
5 COMMITTEE FILLING THE VACANCY BY A PUBLIC NOTICE THAT INCLUDES:
6 1. THE CENTRAL COMMITTEE’S INTENT TO MEET TO FILL
7 THE VACANCY;
8 2. THE TIME AND PLACE OF ANY MEETINGS TO BE HELD
9 TO DISCUSS OR VOTE ON THE FILLING OF THE VACANCY;
10 3. THE PROCESS FOR FILLING THE VACANCY; AND
11 4. THE MANNER IN WHICH INDIVIDUALS MAY APPLY TO
12 FILL THE VACANCY.
13 (2) THE NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1)(II) OF THIS
14 SUBSECTION SHALL BE TRANSLATED INTO A LANGUAGE OTHER THAN ENGLISH IF
15 THE LOCAL BOARD FOR THE COUNTY IN WHICH THE CENTRAL COMMITTEE IS
16 LOCATED IS REQUIRED TO TRANSLATE ELECTION MATERIALS INTO THAT LANGUAGE
17 UNDER § 203 OF THE FEDERAL VOTING RIGHTS ACT.
18 (C) ALL APPLICATIONS SUBMITTED TO A CENTRAL COMMITTEE TO FILL A
19 VACANCY SHALL:
20 (1) BE POSTED ONLINE PROMPTLY AFTER THE APPLICATION
21 DEADLINE BY THE COUNTY CENTRAL COMMITTEE OR THE STATE CENTRAL
22 COMMITTEE OF THE POLITICAL PARTY; AND
23 (2) REMAIN POSTED ONLINE UNTIL AT LEAST 30 DAYS AFTER THE
24 CENTRAL COMMITTEE VOTES ON AN INDIVIDUAL TO FILL THE VACANCY.
25 (D) THE CENTRAL COMMITTEE SHALL HOLD A PUBLIC MEETING TO
26 INTERVIEW THE INDIVIDUALS WHO APPLIED TO FILL THE VACANCY.
27 (E) A MEETING HELD BY A CENTRAL COMMITTEE TO DISCUSS OR VOTE ON
28 FILLING A VACANCY SHALL BE:
29 (1) OPEN TO THE PUBLIC; AND

HOUSE BILL 237 3
1 (2) ANNOUNCED AT LEAST 3 DAYS BEFORE THE MEETING.
2 (F) (1) THE VOTE BY A CENTRAL COMMITTEE TO CHOOSE AN INDIVIDUAL
3 TO FILL A VACANCY SHALL BE:
4 (I) BY ROLL CALL VOTE OR BY SIGNED BALLOTS; AND
5 (II) IN A MEETING OPEN TO THE PUBLIC.
6 (2) A MEMBER OF THE CENTRAL COMMITTEE WHO HAS APPLIED TO
7 FILL THE VACANCY SHALL RECUSE THEMSELVES FROM:
8 (I) ADMINISTERING THE PROCESS OF FILLING THE VACANCY,
9 INCLUDING ADVERTISING THE VACANCY, REVIEWING APPLICATIONS, AND
10 INTERVIEWING CANDIDATES; AND
11 (II) VOTING ON THE INDIVIDUAL TO FILL THE VACANCY.
12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
13 October 1, 2025.
